Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman presented her 8th Union Budget to the Parliament on 1st February 2025. The Budget covered different proposals for the Indian Economy.
In this video, Abhi and Niyu have covered important points from the Budget proposals, explained how the new tax slabs and rebate works, and explain how the Union Budget works. 

Here are some of the important proposals mentioned in the Budget:
* Nuclear Energy Mission
* Support to Footwear Industry (both leather and non leather)
* Makhana Board for Bihar
* Support to Make in India Toys
* Shipbuilding Financial Assistance Policy
* Policy to procure pulses directly from farmers on contract farming basis
* Modified UDAN scheme
* National Repository of Indian Knowledge books
* Bharat TRADENET
* High Level Committee for non financial sector regulatory reforms

Sources: 
Economic Survey: https://www.indiabudget.gov.in/economicsurvey/
Budget: https://www.indiabudget.gov.in/

In this video, Abhi and Niyu have covered important points from the Budget proposals, explained how the new tax slabs and rebate works, and explain how the Union Budget works. 

Here are some of the important proposals mentioned in the Budget:
* Nuclear Energy Mission
* Support to Footwear Industry (both leather and non leather)
* Makhana Board for Bihar
* Support to Make in India Toys
* Shipbuilding Financial Assistance Policy
* Policy to procure pulses directly from farmers on contract farming basis
* Modified UDAN scheme
* National Repository of Indian Knowledge books
* Bharat TRADENET
* High Level Committee for non financial sector regulatory reforms

snippet.title: Saraswati Vandana | Shreya Ghoshal
snippet.description:
Shreya Ghoshal embarks on a new musical journey with devotion at its heart, beginning with a Saraswati Vandana‚Äîa sacred ode to the goddess of wisdom, music, and the arts. This newly composed hymn beautifully captures the essence of Ma Saraswati‚Äôs grace, symbolising the purity of mind, intellectual and spiritual enlightenment and creativity. Enriched by the ethereal voice of Shreya Ghoshal, whose pristine vocal texture brings unmatched beauty, the melody flows like a sacred offering, uplifting the soul and invoking the goddess‚Äôs blessings. Her vocals seamlessly weave into the poignant notes of Sarod and the lush choral arrangements. This musical offering is an invitation to immerse in the profound peace and inspiration that Ma Saraswati personifies.

Singer - Shreya Ghoshal

snippet.title: Dilli Ki Winters | The Paayal Jain
snippet.description:
Hey Guys , 
Hope you enjoy this winter video . We love you so much .

Click on Link To Buy Himalaya Serum - https://amzn.to/3EaXbc2

This video shows different behaviours of Indians during winters . Dilli Ki Winters is extreme .  This is a very comic and relatable video. When the temperature is falling and the heaters , hot water bags , heating pads , sweaters , sweatshirts , hoodies , coats , jackets , scarfs mufflers , gloves , thermals , socks , monkey caps , boots , comes to beat the cold especially if it's delhi winters . College exams during winters , School Board Exams with hot coffee or tea travelling by metro bikes in thand , shopping from sarojini market for latest winter fashion , planning winter trip to hills with friends to see snow , cause snowfall , bonfire with friends is the best time . indian moms covering kids in multiple layers of warm clothes to avoid cold and flue , Feeding winter green leafy vegetables , hara saag and  enjoying thand me gajar ka halwa , lazy winters in bed watching shows Tv serials anupama or christmas movies with hot chocolate , chai , heater , blanket perfect cosy environment .  Buying school winter uniform for kids , Mothers and their millions of excuses when it comes to exercising or changing life in sardiyan that sardi bht pad rhi he and alot more . All these winter problems that we all indians in winters face .

This video is filled with such memories and situations we all have been in. 
Relish and Relive your Memories.. You will love this .
Do share it with your friends and family  .. Comment down your Fav Part, 
Like, Share and

snippet.title: Celebrating the Year of the Snake! üêç Clash of Clans New Season
snippet.description:
Legendary snakes of the Clash lands are ushering in an age of celebration! Get in on the Lunar festivities, unleash mystical Snake Heroes, and start training for some ludicrously Lunar challenges and Events ahead! Visit the sky-high home of the ancient elemental snakes with the Year of the Snake Legendary Scenery and transform your Village into a serene sanctuary where the celebrations never end!

Follow us on our Socials!
Twitter ‚ñ∫ https://twitter.com/ClashofClans/
Instagram ‚ñ∫ https://www.instagram.com/clashofclans 
Facebook ‚ñ∫ https://www.facebook.com/ClashofClans 
TikTok ‚ñ∫ https://www.tiktok.com/@clashofclans

Attack. Defend. Strategize. Download for free for mobile devices. supr.cl/PlayClashOfClans

From rage-¬≠filled Barbarians with glorious mustaches to pyromaniac wizards, raise your own army and lead your clan to victory! Build your village to fend off raiders, battle against millions of players worldwide, and forge a powerful clan with others to destroy enemy clans.
PLEASE NOTE! Clash of Clans is free to download and play, however some game items can also be purchased for real money 

Also, under our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy, you must be at least 13 years of age to play or download Clash of Clans.
A network connection is also required.

FEATURES
- Build your village into an unbeatable fortress 
- Raise your own army of Barbarians, Archers, Hog Riders, Wizards, Dragons and other mighty fighters
- Battle with players worldwide and take their Trophies
- Join together with other players to form the ultimate Clan
- Fight against rival Clans in epic Clan Wars 
- Build 18 unique units with multiple levels of upgrades
- Discover your favorite attacking army from countless combinations of troops, spells, Heroes and Clan reinforcements 
- Defend your village with a multitude of Cannons, Towers, Mortars, Bombs, Traps and Walls
- Fight against the Goblin King in a campaign through the realm

Chief, are you having problems? Visit https://help.supercellsupport.com/clash-of-clans/en/

Vallavanukku Pullum Aayudham  is a 2014 Indian Tamil-language action comedy film directed by Srinath and released by Studio Green on 9 May 2014. A remake of S. S. Rajamouli's successful Telugu film Maryada Ramanna (2010) which was based on Buster Keaton's Our Hospitality (1923),[1] the film was jointly produced by PVP Cinema and Santhanam, who also played the lead role in it, alongside newcomer Ashna Zaveri. The music was composed by Siddharth Vipin.

AFSOS (Lyrics)

A 1

Haan 
Teri yaadan yaadan 
Teri yaadan le ke betha 
Kai raatan raatan

Par aaj
Ena raatan picho
Meinu sab sach nazar ae aunda
Kivein akhan akhan?

B 1

Jo guroor si 
Oh fizool si 
Meinu aaj pata laga 
Ki kasoor si 

Mere dil de noor 
Main si mash-hoor 
Tenu karta dur 
Oh, bekasoor!

Kinj gairan nu 
Main apna mann 
Mileya mere apne nu 
Gair ban

Eh taan zaroor 
Dil karta choor
Tera

C 1 

Te haan
Main duniya vekhi 
Tere dil nu vekh na paya 
Main jhalla jhalla 

Karda si
Wadeya nawan di
Gallan gallan

Hun ethe
Marda janda 
Main kalla kalla

A 2

Hun kyun 
Afsos hoya?
Hun ki fayeda?
Milna ni
Je chahaan chahaan

Main hun
Ghadiya de hath te
Kivein modha 
Rukh samay da 
Te rahaan rahaan?

D 

Chand pal do pal 
Teri sunda battan je 

Tere nal hi 
Sab katda rattan je 

Tere hanju dekhda 
Vich barsattan je

Kitte karda teh 
Eh dil di vattan je 

B 2

Kaisi shaam si
Tere naam si 
Jo padheya na main
Ki pegham si?

Main hairan si
Naadan si
Kis gallon meri jaan
Pareshan si?

Tenu hasde vekh ke
Baar baar
Tenu puchi na main kadey tere
Dil di saar

Tera intezar, 
Meri samjho baar 
Kidda katey ne tu din metho 
Haar haar?

C 2

Haan
Jo pyaar si tera
Thoda vi samajh na paya 
Main jhalla jhalla 

Haan
Eh dil pachtave 
Tere bin hun reh na pave 
Eh kalla kalla

A 3

Hun kyun 
Afsos hoya?
Hun ki fayeda?
Milna ni
Je chahaan chahaan

Main hun
Ghadiya de hath te
Kivein modha 
Rukh samay da 
Te rahaan rahaan?

Te rahaan rahaan
Te rahaan rahaan

snippet.description:

Moreover, Khawaja and Smith both scored centuries and are still unbeaten.

snippet.title: SNAIL FRY | NATHAI VARUVAL | Snail Recipe Cooking and Eating in Village | Healthy Village Recipes
snippet.description:
Discover the art of traditional Snail Fry (Nathai Varuval) cooking in the heart of the village! üêå‚ú® This unique recipe combines fresh, locally sourced snails with a blend of aromatic spices, creating a mouthwatering dish that‚Äôs as healthy as it is flavorful.

Watch as we prepare this delicacy from scratch, using simple yet time-tested techniques over a firewood stove. Every step showcases the charm of village cooking, from cleaning the snails to frying them to perfection.

What‚Äôs in the Recipe:

Fresh snails straight from nature
A medley of traditional spices
Gingelly oil and hand-ground masala for authentic flavor

This video is not just about cooking; it celebrates culture, community, and the joy of sharing delicious food. Stay until the end for a delightful tasting session that will leave you craving this wholesome delicacy!

snippet.title: Pre-booked Breakfast On Air India Express!! ‚úàÔ∏èüçΩÔ∏è
snippet.description:
Pre-booked a ‚Çπ650 breakfast on my Air India Express flight from Bengaluru to Delhi‚Äîwas it worth it? First, a little heartbreak‚Äîwhere‚Äôs the iconic artificial waterfall at T2? Anyway, after boarding the new Boeing 737, I found myself in a middle seat with no window (tough life). Took off with a limited outside view and soon, food arrived! T

he masala tea? Too watered down. The cheese omelette? A bit eggy at first but got better. The hara bhara kebab? Surprisingly soft and moist. The baked beans? Classic, soft, and mushy. 

But the real winner? The banana chocolate cake‚Äîdense, balanced, and a big thumbs up! Wrapped it all up with some water before dozing off, only to wake up to great weather in Delhi. Another flight, another meal reviewed‚Äîsubscribe for more food and travel adventures! 

#AirIndiaExpress #FlightFood #InflightMeals #TravelDiaries #FoodReview #AviationLovers #OmeletteLove #MasalaTea #MiddleSeatStruggles #PlaneFoodie #DelhiDiaries #BangaloreAirport #SkyHigh #FoodAdventure #DCTEats

---
This channel is owned, operated, and managed by, Contagious Online Media Network Private Limited.

Medical school aspirants know the grind like no one else. From **NEET prep** to the **MBBS dream**, the journey is anything but easy. It starts with endless hours of **study grind**, flipping through **NCERT Bible** pages, and juggling between **mock test anxiety** and **last-minute revision**. The **topper mindset** isn‚Äôt just about getting high scores; it‚Äôs about surviving the **coaching life**, decoding **mnemonics & shortcuts**, and finding ways to stay motivated despite the sleepless nights. Every medical aspirant has promised themselves **"Kal se serious"** at least once, only to be distracted by **procrastination**, the eternal enemy of every student. But when the dream is to wear that **white coat** and hold a **stethoscope**, there‚Äôs no room for giving up.  

The real adventure begins when you step into **medical college**, where the excitement of the **first dissection** is mixed with the terror of **viva** exams. Walking into the **anatomy lab struggles** feels like entering an unknown world, and **cadaver room stories** are enough to haunt even the bravest students. Then comes the **8 AM lectures**, where half the class is either sleeping or relying on **coffee-fueled nights** to stay awake. But nothing prepares you for the **36-hour shifts** of clinical rotations, where exhaustion meets **ward duty blues**, and the real learning begins. **Sleep vs. study dilemma** becomes an everyday battle, and some days, **mental breakdowns before exams** feel inevitable.  

Yet, amidst all the chaos, **study group saviors** make the journey bearable. There‚Äôs always that one friend who calls during **exam panic mode**, asking **"Bhai tune kya padha?"**, as if cramming last minute will change fate. **Late-night library sessions** turn into deep discussions about life, and **seniors vs. juniors bonding** happens over shared struggles and survival tips. Even the **professors‚Äô legendary one-liners** become inside jokes among students. And despite the stress, **college fests & stress relief** moments remind every medical student why they chose this path in the first place.  

But medical school isn‚Äôt just about books and tests‚Äîit‚Äôs also about expectations. **Parents‚Äô expectations** loom large, with the constant reminder of **"Doctor ban jao, phir aish hi aish"**, while reality proves otherwise. The fear of **imposter syndrome** creeps in, making students question if they truly belong here. Some dream of the day they‚Äôll finally attend **convocation day**, while others are just trying to get through the next **clinical rotation** without passing out from exhaustion. The road to becoming a doctor is paved with challenges, but the **determination to achieve it** keeps every medical aspirant going.  

Because at the end of the day, it‚Äôs not just about **cracking NEET** or surviving **medical textbooks overload**‚Äîit‚Äôs about the passion to heal, the courage to face setbacks, and the resilience to keep going. Whether it‚Äôs the struggle of remembering every tiny detail from **pharmacology** or the joy of finally making sense of **pathology**, every step in this journey shapes the future **doctors of tomorrow**. So to every **medical school aspirant** out there, battling through **NCERT Bible**, surviving **mock test anxiety**, and chasing that **MBBS dream**‚Äîyou‚Äôre not alone. The struggle is real, but so is the reward. Keep going! üí™üöÄ

snippet.title: Filmymoji || Middle Class Madhu || Mandala Deeksha || Final Episode || MCM
snippet.description:
Filmymoji Middle Class Madhu  Mandala Deeksha Final Episode MCM

The much-awaited climax of the Deeksha series on the FilmyMoji channel is here! In this gripping final episode, Madhu and his friends, along with Sarada Subbarao, embark on an intense spiritual journey‚Äîthe Ayyappa Deeksha‚Äîculminating in a pilgrimage to the sacred Sabarimala Temple.

Plot Summary:

As the journey begins, the group faces multiple physical and emotional hurdles. They endure the rigorous 41-day Deeksha, following strict rules of celibacy, vegetarianism, and discipline. Throughout the journey, humor and camaraderie shine, especially with the presence of 1A Master, who adds his signature comic relief to the otherwise spiritual and serious narrative.

Upon reaching Sabarimala, they experience the challenge of climbing the sacred 18 steps (Pathinettu Padi), which symbolize the ultimate test of devotion. The emotional and spiritual highs of the journey are depicted beautifully, with divine moments that leave a lasting impact on the viewers.

Meanwhile, Ganesh, a key character in the story, faces an unexpected twist. Will he be able to complete his Deeksha successfully? Will the group have a fulfilling pilgrimage? The episode ties up all loose ends with a mix of devotion, comedy, and life lessons.

Why You Should Watch:

Spiritual Significance: A heartfelt depiction of Ayyappa Deeksha and the power of devotion.

Comedy & Emotions: The perfect blend of humor and sentiment, making it a wholesome watch.

Friendship & Brotherhood: A strong message about togetherness and faith.

Climax with a Twist: A surprising turn that keeps you engaged till the very end.


Don‚Äôt miss out on this emotional and uplifting finale! Swamiye Saranam Ayyappa!
